parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning instrument cluster can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: All warning lights on the instrument panel come on and off
gauges fluctuate
fuel gauge drops to empty
and the engine stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: All warning lights on the instrument panel come on and off
gauges fluctuate
fuel gauge drops to empty
and the engine stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning airbag system can cause the passenger airbag to not deploy in the event of an accident, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Passenger airbag off light on the dashboard illuminates
and the airbag system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut off randomly, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off randomly while driving
gauges drop to zero and then slowly return
warning lights flash
warning chime sounds repeatedly
sudden power loss to the engine
engine goes through a start cycle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch assembly can cause the clutch pedal to feel hard or difficult to shift, making it challenging to drive, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels hard or difficult to shift
the gear selector is extremely difficult to shift in and out of gear
the hydraulic clutch assembly is not releasing
causing hard shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's gauges (gas
speed
tach) go to zero and flutter up and down
the vehicle stalls
the horn sticks or doesn't work properly
the ignition switch doesn't work with multiple keys on the keyring
wiggling the key can stop the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel vacuum problem can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle feels like it's losing power
all the lights on the dash are lit up
the vehicle loses steering
the engine jerks and pulls
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Lower Control Arm Bushing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front lower control arm bushing can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle requires frequent replacement of the front lower control arm bushings
even with low mileage.
